{"id":"1710.08190","submitter":"Yoshito Ishiki","authors":"Yoshito Ishiki","title":"Quasi-symmetric invariant properties of Cantor metric spaces","comments":"To appear in Annales de l'Institut Fourier","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.MG math.GN","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  For metric spaces, the doubling property, the uniform disconnectedness, and\nthe uniform perfectness are known as quasi-symmetric invariant properties. The\nDavid-Semmes uniformization theorem states that if a compact metric space\nsatisfies all the three properties, then it is quasi-symmetrically equivalent\nto the middle-third Cantor set. We say that a Cantor metric space is standard\nif it satisfies all the three properties; otherwise, it is exotic. In this\npaper, we conclude that for each of exotic types the class of all the conformal\ngauges of Cantor metric spaces has continuum cardinality. As a byproduct of our\nstudy, we state that there exists a Cantor metric space with prescribed\nHausdorff dimension and Assouad dimension.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 23 Oct 2017 10:36:48 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 27 Nov 2017 04:49:24 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 9 Jan 2018 04:17:58 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Wed, 28 Feb 2018 01:21:29 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Fri, 8 Feb 2019 09:03:29 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-02-11"}
